I have arrived early yesterday morning - at the Corps HQ but am only now getting into the work at all properly. Some people have this gift of handing over, others with the best will in the world have not.This corps has been the most successful hitherto, therefore its work should be on sound lines, and it is interesting seeing a new formation at work tho' it lacks the excitement of a Divisional office.

I believe now that my message to ( Edward ?) was not correct, tho' true of the actual situation. There appears to be the greatest difficulty in getting the staff out tho' we are assured there is plenty at home.
Ones facilities for writing letters are worse than ever before as 2 of us sit at the same table - not always the same 2 tho' now i have more or less settle my own place. This & having no letters to inspire me will make this a very dull letter.
My work seems likely to be mainly in the office but i hope to get some exercise daily.
I did not say good by to  G N as he was out and declined to say goodby on the previous day. I am not sure that this was not deliberate on his part. I n any case I really cannot say i am sorry to leave him. He is I think the most naturally selfish man I have ever been brought into close touch with and really this alleviates my regret to some extent, tho' I still feel as if I had deserted RN in his hour of need. It is, I am told absolutely certain that the only excuse for refusing any appointment is lack of qualification and tho' it is quite likely i may show myself  (unfit??) after trial I am not going to admit it before. No time for more as I am off to visit the "German" lines in a motor ! Address Lt COl GS attached HQ 15 Corps
Yours f w
WB Spender 
-->
                

                
            </change>
        
