                    Page 6417 modified:
                    <!-- 
D1633/1/1/359
24 July
My Pv
I have arrived - early yesterday morning - at the Corps HQ, but am only now getting into the work at all  properly. Some people have the gift of handing over, others with the best will in the world have not. This corps has been the most successful hitherto, & therefore its work should be on sound lines, & it is interesting seeing a new formation at work tho' it lacks the excitement of a Divisional office. 
I believe now that my message to Sredurand was not correct, tho true of the actual situation. This appears to be the greatest difficulty in getting the stuff out tho' we are assured there is plenty at home. One's facilities for writing letters are worse than ever before as 2 of us sit at the same table - not always the same 2 tho' now I have more or less settled my own place. This & having no  letters to inspire me will make this a very dull letter. 
 My work seems likely to be mainly in the office but I hope to get some exercise daily.
I did not say goodbye to GN as he was out & declined to say goodbye on the previous day. I am not sure that this was not deliberate on his part. In any case I really cannot say I am sorry to leave him. He is I think the most naturally selfish man I have ever been brought into close touch with, & really this alleviates my regret to some extent, tho' I still feel as if I had deserted Rex in his hour of need, It is , I am told absolutely certain that the only excuse for refusing any appointment is lack of qualification & tho' it is quite likely I may show myself unfitted after trial I am not going to admit it before. 
No time for more as I am off to visit the "German" lines in a motor ! 
Address Lt Col GS  attached  HQ 15 Corps
Your b w 
WB Spender
PS: Some folks put RA &; omit GS on my letters which may lead to my not getting them now. 
-->
                

                
            </change>
        
