            <text type="letter" decls="#corresp1">
                <body>
                    

<opener><dateline><date>24 July</date></dateline>
<salute>My Pr</salute></opener>
<p>I have arrived - early yesterday morning - at the Corps HQ, but am 
<lb/> only now getting into the work at all  properly. Some people have the 
<lb/>gift of handing over, others with the best will in the world have not.
<lb/> This corps has been the most successful hitherto, &amp; therefore its work
<lb/> should be on sound lines, &amp; it is interesting seeing a new formation at 
<lb/>work tho' it lacks the excitement of a Divisional office.</p> 

<p>I believe now that my message to <unclear>Sr edward</unclear>  was not correct, tho
<lb/> true of the actual situation. There appears to be the greatest difficulty
<lb/> in getting the stuff out tho' we are assured there is plenty at home.</p> 
<p>One's facilities for writing letters are worse than ever before as 2
<lb/> of us sit at the same table - not always the same 2 tho' now I have more
<lb/> or less settled my own place. This &amp; having no <del>one</del> letters to inspire me will
<lb/> make this a very dull letter.</p> 
<p>My work seems likely to be mainly in the office but I hope to get some exercise daily.</p>
<p>I did not say goodbye to GN as he was out &amp; declined to
<lb/> say goodbye on the previous day. I am not sure that this was not
<lb/> deliberate on his part. In any case I really cannot say I am sorry
<lb/> to leave him. He is I think the most naturally selfish man I have ever
<lb/> been brought into close touch with, &amp; really this alleviates my regret
<lb/> to some extent, tho' I still feel as if I had deserted Rex in his hour of need
<lb/> It is, I am told absolutely certain that the only excuse for refusing any
<lb/> appointment is lack of qualification &amp; tho' it is quite likely I may show
<lb/> myself unfitted after trial I am not going to admit it before.</p>
 <p>No time for more as I am off to visit the "German"
<lb/> lines in a motor ! Address Lt Col GS.  attached HQ 15 Corps.</p> 

<closer><salute>Your b w</salute>  
<signed>WB Spender </signed></closer>

 <p>PS: Some folks put RA &amp; omit GS on my letters which
<lb/> may lead to my not getting them now.</p>
        
    

    
                </body>
            </text>

        
            
        

         

